The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 05 November is 95,905 (11,053.6 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 31 October, there were 4,817 new confirmed cases (555.2 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 24 October, there were 4,675 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 3% (142 extra cases).
